          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Ser216Profs*50) in the POLG gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. This variant is not present in population databases (ExAC no frequency). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals with POLG-related disease. Loss-of-function variants in POLG are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 18546365, 21696159, 27987238). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
